quest_title: If for two matrices \(A\) and \(B\), the matrix multiplication is anti commutative, \( (A+B)^2 = \)
explanation_txt:
If the matrix multiplication is anti-commutative, \(AB = -BA \Rightarrow AB + BA =0 \)

So, \( (A+B)^2 = (A+B)(A+B) = A^2 + AB + BA + B^2 = A^2 + B^2 \)

Also, \( (A-B)^2 = (A-B)(A-B) = A^2 - AB - BA + B^2 = A^2 + B^2 - (AB+BA) = A^2 + B^2 \)

So, option (c) is correct.

quest_title: Three faradays of electricity are passed through molten \(Al_{2} O_{3} \), aqueous solution of \(CuSO_{4} \) and molten \(NaCl\) taken in different electrolytic cells. The amount of \(Al,\, Cu\) and \(Na\) deposited at the cathodes will be in the ratio of
explanation_txt:
At cathode : \(Al^{3+} +3e^{-} \to Al\)

\[E_{Al} =\cfrac{{\rm Atomic\; mass}}{3} \]

At cathode : \(Cu^{2+} +2e^{-} \to Cu\)

\[E_{Cu} =\cfrac{{\rm Atomic}\, {\rm mass}}{2} \]

At cathode : \(Na^{+} +e^{-} \to Na\)

\[E_{Na} =\cfrac{{\rm Atomic}\, {\rm mass}}{1} \]

For the passage of 3 faraday;

mole atoms of \(Al\) deposited = 1

mole atoms of \(\textit{Cu}\) deposited \(=\cfrac{1\times 3}{2} =1.5\)

mole atoms of \(\textit{Na}\) deposited \(=1\times 3=3\).

quest_title: A boy standing on a long rail road car throws a ball straight upwards. The car is moving on the horizontal road with an acceleration of 1 m/s\({}^{2}\) . and projection velocity in the vertical direction is 10 m/s. The distance on ground behind boy at which ball hit is
explanation_txt:
For ball

\(\begin{array}{l}{0=\mathrm{uT}-\cfrac{1}{2} \mathrm{gT}^{2}} \\ {\mathrm{T}=\cfrac{2 \mathrm{u}}{\mathrm{g}}=\cfrac{2 \times 10}{10}=2 \mathrm{sec}}\end{array}\)

For car

\(\mathrm{S}=\cfrac{1}{2} \mathrm{at}^{2}=\cfrac{1}{2} \times 1 \times 2^{2}=2\)

\(\therefore\) Distance = 2m
